  "title": "Accountant / Senior Accounts Executive",
  "description": "<h2>Accountant / Senior Accounts Executive</h2><p><strong>(3-Month Contract | Potential Extension / Permanent Role)  </strong></p><p>We are a growing manufacturing company seeking a <strong>reliable and experienced Accountant / Senior Accounts Executive</strong> to join our team, reporting to the <strong>CFO and GM (HR)</strong>.</p><h3>Key Responsibilities</h3><p><strong>Accounting & Financial Management</strong></p><ul><li><p>Manage partial sets of accounts (AP, AR, GL) and handle full sets independently when required</p></li><li><p>Ensure timely <strong>GST submissions</strong>, monthly closing, and management reporting</p></li><li><p>Support budgeting, cash flow management, cost analysis, and financial planning</p></li><li><p>Assist with year-end closing, audits, and statutory reporting in compliance with <strong>SFRS</strong></p></li><li><p>Perform bank reconciliations and monitor cash flow and payment schedules</p></li><li><p>Prepare ad-hoc financial analysis and reports</p></li><li><p>Support inventory costing, fixed asset tracking, and job costing</p></li></ul><p><strong>General Support</strong></p><ul><li><p>Assist with administrative and compliance-related tasks as required</p></li><li><p>Support HR–Finance coordination, documentation, and regulatory submissions when needed</p></li></ul><h3>Job Requirements</h3><ul><li><p>Advanced Diploma or Bachelor’s Degree in Accounting, Finance, Business Administration, or related fields</p></li><li><p>Minimum <strong>3 years of relevant experience</strong>, with at least <strong>2 consecutive years in the same company</strong></p></li><li><p>Knowledge of <strong>SFRS and Singapore statutory regulations</strong> is an advantage</p></li><li><p>Strong proficiency in accounting systems, <strong>Microsoft Excel</strong>, and MS Office</p></li><li><p>Knowledge of Singapore employment regulations, work pass procedures, and WSH policies is advantageous</p></li><li><p>Willing to work <strong>one Saturday per month</strong></p></li><li><p>Candidates with <strong>at least 2 years of supervisory experience</strong> and <strong>with HR background</strong> will be viewed favourably.<br /></p></li></ul><h3>Contract / Permanent Opportunity</h3><p>High-performing candidates may be offered an <strong>extended contract (6–12 months)</strong> or a <strong>permanent position</strong>, subject to performance and available opportunities.</p><p></p>",
